* Mawer Fund returns are calculated after management fees and operating expenses have been deducted.** This information is not available because the Fund has not yet completed a Financial year.*** The Mawer New Canada Fund is capped to new and existing mutual fund investors. Additional units of this fund are not available for purchase.† MERs are as at December 31, 2016.†† The Fund’s MER is made up of the management fee and operating expenses. The Fund’s annual management fee is 0.60% of the Fund’s value. Because this fund is new, its operating expenses are relatively large in comparison to the fund’s assets. The management of Mawer has committed to subsidize the operating expenses of the Fund from its inception so that the MER is no more than 0.75%. Management plans to review the subsidy periodically with the intent to remove the subsidy once the MER of the Fund has stabilized from asset growth at approximately 0.75%. After the subsidized period ends the actual MER for the Fund may be higher than 0.75%.‡ Funds with less than three years of performance history are not rated.‡‡ As of April 30th, 2013, Morningstar will no longer calculate a Morningstar Ratings™ for money market funds. 









